{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"59b50708-74f7-472e-92f8-582b64625869","content":"Here's the skip attribute for each framework:\n\n**MSTest**\n```csharp\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**xUnit**\n```csharp\n[Fact(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\n// or for theories:\n[Theory(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**NUnit**\n```csharp\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**TUnit**\n```csharp\n[Skip(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\nAll four will report the test as \"skipped\" (not failed) in test results, with your reason message visible in the output.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"045f7f46-3de6-4cce-b7a9-734741377336","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about the correct attribute syntax to skip tests with a reason message in each of the four .NET test frameworks: MSTest, xUnit, NUnit, and TUnit. Let me provide this from my knowledge.","outputTokens":217,"requestId":"BC23:21D6AD:23C6BB:29F112:69FA9399"},"id":"27c0a951-a8a0-4678-b83f-20e4e90f9b64","timestamp":"2026-05-06T01:04:31.322Z","parentId":"1cc34898-0c81-4870-8070-9844eaba38d6"}
